Employers are scheduling same-day interviews, noted on a whiteboard, as international students queue for advice on visa sponsorship requirements. Volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures. The aroma of coffee and catered snacks spreads from the lounge as students exit with tote bags and stacks of business cards. Small groups analyze which recruiters seemed most enthusiastic, while others mark target employers on the event map. A post-event survey link flashes on the monitors near the exit.
